"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The custom distance metric function `get_point_distance` is not correctly used with DBSCAN. The `metric` parameter in DBSCAN expects a string identifier of a metric or a callable that takes two arrays as input. The `get_point_distance` function is designed to take two Point objects, not arrays.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n<     return float(euclidean_distances([p1], [p2])[0, 0])\\n---\\n>     return float(euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])[0, 0])\\n28c28\\n< clustering = DBSCAN(metric=get_point_distance).fit(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\\n---\\n> clustering = DBSCAN(metric='euclidean').fit(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\"\n}"